NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: I summed all the full day counts from 5/6, 6/4, 6/5, 6/7-6/12, 6/18-6/22, and 7/6-7/13 (this was all the full days that could be salvaged from the motherboard failure) this totaled 792 sockeye, I applied the DVR detection rate from 2011 (.925) and the sum of daily proportions for the days with complete counts (0.29952) to estimate a run-size of 2,859 assuming a normal run-time.  An early run-time would yield an estimate of  4,821.  (Umbrella Estimate was 4,550).
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: taken from HGMP extension letter appendix (2015). (umbrellaNOR + ozetteRunSize)/ozetteRunSize. This is likely an underestimate due to other hatchery fish (e.g. Big River) and in lake pre-spawn mortality.

NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: I summed all of the full day counts from 5/22-6/14 and 7/3-8/1, 2,682 sockeye upstream, applied a .925 detection rate, and assumed .5488 of the run passed during these days based on the average timing from 2000-2011, to estimate a run-size of 5,282.
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: MFM 2014 unpublished escapement estimate updated in 2015/16 annual report (see 2014 Umbrella Excel file)

NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: I summed all of the full day counts from 5/22-6/14 and 6/20-8/5; 4,692 sockeye upstream, applied a .925 detection rate, and assumed 0.7409 of the run passed during these days based on the average timing from 2000-2011, to estimate a run-size of 6,846.
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: MFM 2015 and 2016 LOS RMP Report

NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: I summed all of the full day counts from 6/17-7/6; 3,486 sockeye upstream, applied a .925 detection rate, and assumed .2883 of the run passed during these days based on the average timing from 2000-2011, to estimate a run-size of 13,073
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: MFM 2015 and 2016 LOS RMP Report

NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: [ARIS] From Keith Denton report, 5,036 sockeye estimated between 5/11 and 8/11.  Timing data from 2000-2011; indicate that 0.9279 enter the lake from 5/11-8/12, so 5036/0.9279 =5427; [DVR] I assumed half of the fish on 6/21 were counted, then summed 6/22-7/19 full day counts, 2,385 sockeye; Used the ARIS estimates
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: MFM 2016-2019 LOS RMP Report

NWR_POPULATION_NAME: Sockeye Salmon (Ozette Lake ESU) - Ozette Lake
SPAWNER_NOTES: [ARIS ONLY]  I used only whole entire days where data were collected, I removed questionable days and data reviewed by PKB- net upstream migrants 2,140.  I then determined the proportion of the run that on average enters the lake for the days with data 0.63402 to estimate 3,375 sockeye.
HATCHERY_FRACTION_NOTES: MFM 2016-2019 LOS RMP Report
